deck: Leader of the Leopards Sun Cult.
name: King Ekeko

deck: A genetically engineered gorilla from the Horizon Lunar Colony, Winston was raised to have the heart and soul of a scientist. Since coming to Earth he joined Overwatch.
name: Winston

deck: Fellow student and not-so-potential-love-interest to Bailey Hoskins.
description:
Origin

A student.

Creation

Written by Max Bemis and drawn by Michael Walsh.

Major Story Arcs

Unbeknownst to Jennifer, Bailey Hoskins has taken her picture to add to his collection of potential girlfriends. Jennifer, however, is goth and purportedly listens to Burzum, a band way to heavy for Bailey to get into (something about the lead singer being a Nazi murderer...). Jennifer is quickly dismissed as a potential girlfriend.
name: Jennifer Brody

description:
Origin

A student that has a penchant for alternative things.

Creation

Written by Max Bemis and drawn by Michael Walsh

Major Story Arcs

Bailey Hoskins pulls up a pictures on his phone and ponders whether he has a shot with Kate. It is pointed out, however, that Bailey is a bit of a square in comparison to Kate, as she breaks rules puts value on knowing about obscure musicians. Kate is dismissed as a potential girlfriend.
name: Kate Carter

deck: Student and way out of Bailey Hoskins' league.
description:
Origin

A popular student.

Creation

Written by Max Bemis and drawn by Michael Walsh.

Major Story Arcs

Unbeknownst to Amanda, Bailey Hoskins has taken her picture to add to his collection of potential girlfriends. Amanda, however, is far too popular for Bailey and is reported to only go for guys that could double as a model and star quarterback. Due to Bailey lacking certain qualities that automatically qualify him for popularity, Jennifer is dismissed as a potential girlfriend.
name: Amanda Brusk

deck: Young mutant and sister to Riches.
description:
Origin

A young student at Xavier's School that can deteriorate matter at an exponential rate. She is from Florida and is the sister of Riches.

Creation

Written by Max Bemis and drawn by Michael Walsh.

Major Story Arcs

Rags meets Bailey Hoskins shortly after he enrolls in Xavier's School and immediately puts her foot in her mouth by mentioning Bailey's dead parents. She then unintentionally makes Bailey feel more useless after she explains her powers.
name: Rags

deck: Young student and brother to Rags.
description:
Origin

A young student at Xavier's School and can turn anything to gold. He is from Florida and is the brother of Rags.

Creation

Written by Max Bemis and drawn by Michael Walsh.

Major Story Arcs

Riches meets Bailey Hoskins at Xavier's School and brashly explains his mutant power, which only makes Bailey feel worse for having a lame power.
name: Riches

description:
Origin

Fellow classmate and "condescendingly gay" best friend of Bailey Hoskins.

Creation

Written by Max Bemis and drawn by Michael Walsh.

Major Story Arcs

Steve talks Bailey out of trying to get a relationship going with several girls since he has so little in common with them. Instead, Steve points Bailey to someone as apparently bland and mediocre as he is.
name: Steve

description:
Origin

A mutant that chooses to live a simpler life with her family.

Creation

Written by Max Bemis and drawn by Michael Walsh.

Major Story Arcs

After years of shielding her true identity from her son Bailey, Mrs. Hoskins joins Mr. Hoskins in confessing to Bailey that the two of them are mutants. She explains that she has x-ray vision. Mrs. Hoskins accompanies her husband and son to Xavier's School and learns that Bailey is also a mutant, though with a practically useless power. Bailey refuses to enroll in the school and Mr. and Mrs. Hoskins follow him out. Mrs. Hoskins, as well as Mr. Hoskins, is killed without warning when a Sentinel lands on her.
name: Mrs. Hoskins

description:
Origin

Mr. Hoskins is a mutant, but one that lives a quiet life with his wife, Mrs. Hoskins, and son Bailey. Mr. Hoskins claims to have the power to fry an egg on his chest.

Creation

Written by Max Bemis and drawn by Michael Walsh.

Major Story Arcs

After years of living as mutants, Mr. and Mrs. Hoskins decide to "come out" to their son. They are relieved at his acceptance of the fact, but then alarmed at how excited he is that he may be a mutant, too. They take Bailey to Xavier's School and have him tested.

Bailey ends up being a mutant, as well, but likely with the lamest power ever. When Bailey refuses to enroll in the school, Mr. Hoskins tries to comfort his son with the very-dad-like line of "You'll always be the most special kid in the world to us, powers or no powers." Mr. and Mrs. Hoskins are then crushed to death by a Sentinel's foot.
name: Mr. Hoskins
